<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-02-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-02-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="46" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d46">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3691/49.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">President of Honduras</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-02-14"><hi rend="italic">February 14,
                                    1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I thank you for your kind answer to my dispatch of February 11, and I beg
                            you to believe that I highly appreciate the admirable spirit in which
                            you have received and answered the suggestions in the interest of peace.
                            I shall be glad to render any assistance in my power toward working out
                            a practical solution of the interesting problem in accordance with the
                            ideas in which we so perfectly agree.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore
                            Roosevelt.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>